Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV1.abstract: Time left before the message expires, in seconds

Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV1.name: viaBotUserId

Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV5.name: views
Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV5.abstract: Number of times this message was viewed

Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV1.name: mediaAlbumId
Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV1.abstract: Unique identifier of an album this message belongs to. Only photos and videos can be grouped together in albums

Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV1.name: replyMarkup
Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV1.abstract: Reply markup for the message; may be null

Structs/SecretChat.html#/s:5TDLib10Secre.name: isOutbound
Structs/SecretChat.html#/s:5TDLib10Secre.abstract: True, if the chat was created by the current user; otherwise false

Structs/SecretChat.html#/s:5TDLib10Secre.name: ttl
Structs/SecretChat.html#/s:5TDLib10Secre.abstract: Current message Time To Live setting (self-destruct timer) for the chat, in seconds

Structs/SecretChat.html#/s:5TDLib10Secre.name: keyHash
Structs/SecretChat.html#/s:5TDLib10Secre.abstract: Hash of the currently used key for comparison with the hash of the chat partner’s key. This is a string of 36 bytes, which must be used to make a 12x12 square image with a color depth of 4. The first 16 bytes should be used to make a central 8x8 square, while the remaining 20 bytes should be used to construct a 2-pixel-wide border around that square. -Alternatively, the first 32 bytes of the hash can be converted to the hexadecimal format and printed as 32 2-digit hex numbers

Structs/SecretChat.html#/s:5TDLib10Secre.name: layer
Structs/SecretChat.html#/s:5TDLib10Secre.abstract: Secret chat layer; determines features supported by the other client. Video notes are supported if the layer >= 66

Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.name: memberCount
Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Number of members in the supergroup or channel; 0 if unknown

Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Number of users banned from chat; 0 if unknown

Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.name: canGetMembers
Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: True, if members of the chat can be retrieved

Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.name: canSetUsername
Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: True, if the chat can be made public

Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.name: canSetStickerSet

Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: True, if new chat members will have access to old messages. In public supergroups and both public and private channels, old messages are always available, so this option affects only private supergroups. The value of this field is only available for chat administrators

Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.name: upgradedFromMaxMessageId
Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Identifier of the last message in the basic group from which supergroup was upgraded; 0 if none

Structs/Supergroup.html#/s:5TDLib10Super.name: status
Structs/Supergroup.html#/s:5TDLib10Super.abstract: Status of the current user in the supergroup or channel

Structs/Supergroup.html#/s:5TDLib10Super.name: memberCount
Structs/Supergroup.html#/s:5TDLib10Super.abstract: Member count; 0 if unknown. Currently it is guaranteed to be known only if the supergroup or channel was found through SearchPublicChats

Structs/Supergroup.html#/s:5TDLib10Super.name: anyoneCanInvite
Structs/Supergroup.html#/s:5TDLib10Super.abstract: True, if any member of the supergroup can invite other members. This field has no meaning for channels

Structs/Supergroup.html#/s:5TDLib10Super.name: signMessages
Structs/Supergroup.html#/s:5TDLib10Super.abstract: True, if messages sent to the channel should contain information about the sender. This field is only applicable to channels

Structs/Supergroup.html#/s:5TDLib10Super.name: isChannel
Structs/Supergroup.html#/s:5TDLib10Super.abstract: True, if the supergroup is a channel

Structs/Supergroup.html#/s:5TDLib10Super.name: isVerified
Structs/Supergroup.html#/s:5TDLib10Super.abstract: True, if the supergroup or channel is verified

Structs/Supergroup.html#/s:5TDLib10Super.name: restrictionReason
Structs/Supergroup.html#/s:5TDLib10Super.abstract: If non-empty, contains the reason why access to this supergroup or channel must be restricted. Format of the string is {type}: {description}. -{type} Contains the type of the restriction and at least one of the suffixes -all, -ios, -android, or -wp, which describe the platforms on which access should be restricted. (For example, terms-ios-android. {description} contains a human-readable description of the restriction, which can be shown to the user)

Structs/Supergroup.html#/s:5TDLib10Super.name: init(id:username:date:status:memberCount:anyoneCanInvite:signMessages:isChannel:isVerified:restrictionReason:)
Structs/Supergroup.html#/s:5TDLib10Super.abstract: Represents a supergroup or channel with zero or more members (subscribers in the case of channels). From the point of view of the system, a channel is a special kind of a supergroup: only administrators can post and see the list of members, and posts from all administrators use the name and photo of the channel instead of individual names and profile photos. Unlike supergroups, channels can have an unlimited number of subscribers

Structs/RemoteFile.html#/s:5TDLib10Remot.name: id
Structs/RemoteFile.html#/s:5TDLib10Remot.abstract: Remote file identifier, may be empty. Can be used across application restarts or even from other devices for the current user. If the ID starts with http:// or https://, it represents the HTTP URL of the file. TDLib is currently unable to download files if only their URL is known. -If downloadFile is called on such a file or if it is sent to a secret chat, TDLib starts a file generation process by sending updateFileGenerationStart to the client with the HTTP URL in the original_path and #url# as the conversion string. Clients should generate the file by downloading it to the specified location

Structs/RemoteFile.html#/s:5TDLib10Remot.name: isUploadingActive
Structs/RemoteFile.html#/s:5TDLib10Remot.abstract: True, if the file is currently being uploaded (or a remote copy is being generated by some other means)

Structs/RemoteFile.html#/s:5TDLib10Remot.name: isUploadingCompleted
Structs/RemoteFile.html#/s:5TDLib10Remot.abstract: True, if a remote copy is fully available

Structs/RemoteFile.html#/s:5TDLib10Remot.name: uploadedSize
Structs/RemoteFile.html#/s:5TDLib10Remot.abstract: Size of the remote available part of the file; 0 if unknown

Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.name: path
Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.abstract: Local path to the locally available file part; may be empty

Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.name: canBeDownloaded
Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.abstract: True, if it is possible to try to download or generate the file

Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.name: canBeDeleted
Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.abstract: True, if the file can be deleted

Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.name: isDownloadingActive
Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.abstract: True, if the file is currently being downloaded (or a local copy is being generated by some other means)

Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.name: isDownloadingCompleted
Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.abstract: True, if the local copy is fully available

Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.name: downloadedPrefixSize
Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.abstract: If is_downloading_completed is false, then only some prefix of the file is ready to be read. downloaded_prefix_size is the size of that prefix

Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.name: downloadedSize
Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.abstract: Total downloaded file bytes. Should be used only for calculating download progress. The actual file size may be bigger, and some parts of it may contain garbage

Structs/TemporaryPasswordState.html#/s:5.name: hasPassword
Structs/TemporaryPasswordState.html#/s:5.abstract: True, if a temporary password is available

Structs/TemporaryPasswordState.html#/s:5.name: validFor
Structs/TemporaryPasswordState.html#/s:5.abstract: Time left before the temporary password expires, in seconds

Structs/TemporaryPasswordState.html#/s:5.name: init(hasPassword:validFor:)
Structs/TemporaryPasswordState.html#/s:5.abstract: Returns information about the availability of a temporary password, which can be used for payments

Structs/RecoveryEmailAddress.html#/s:5TD.name: init(recoveryEmailAddress:)
Structs/RecoveryEmailAddress.html#/s:5TD.abstract: Contains information about the current recovery email address

Structs/PasswordRecoveryInfo.html#/s:5TD.name: recoveryEmailAddressPattern
Structs/PasswordRecoveryInfo.html#/s:5TD.abstract: Pattern of the email address to which a recovery email was sent

Structs/PasswordRecoveryInfo.html#/s:5TD.name: init(recoveryEmailAddressPattern:)
Structs/PasswordRecoveryInfo.html#/s:5TD.abstract: Contains information available to the user after requesting password recovery

Structs/PasswordState.html#/s:5TDLib13Pa.name: hasPassword
Structs/PasswordState.html#/s:5TDLib13Pa.abstract: True if a 2-step verification password has been set up

Structs/PasswordState.html#/s:5TDLib13Pa.name: passwordHint
Structs/PasswordState.html#/s:5TDLib13Pa.abstract: Hint for the password; can be empty

Structs/PasswordState.html#/s:5TDLib13Pa.name: hasRecoveryEmailAddress
Structs/PasswordState.html#/s:5TDLib13Pa.abstract: True if a recovery email has been set up

Structs/PasswordState.html#/s:5TDLib13Pa.name: unconfirmedRecoveryEmailAddressPattern
Structs/PasswordState.html#/s:5TDLib13Pa.abstract: Pattern of the email address to which a confirmation email was sent

Structs/AuthenticationCodeInfo.html#/s:5.name: phoneNumber
Structs/AuthenticationCodeInfo.html#/s:5.abstract: A phone number that is being authenticated

Structs/AuthenticationCodeInfo.html#/s:5.name: type
Structs/AuthenticationCodeInfo.html#/s:5.abstract: Describes the way the code was sent to the user

Structs/AuthenticationCodeInfo.html#/s:5.name: nextType
Structs/AuthenticationCodeInfo.html#/s:5.abstract: Describes the way the next code will be sent to the user; may be null

Structs/AuthenticationCodeInfo.html#/s:5.name: timeout
Structs/AuthenticationCodeInfo.html#/s:5.abstract: Timeout before the code should be re-sent, in seconds

Structs/AuthenticationCodeInfo.html#/s:5.name: init(phoneNumber:type:nextType:timeout:)
Structs/AuthenticationCodeInfo.html#/s:5.abstract: Information about the authentication code that was sent

Structs/Ok.html#/s:5TDLib2OkVACycfc.name: init()
Structs/Ok.html#/s:5TDLib2OkVACycfc.abstract: An object of this type is returned on a successful function call for certain functions

Structs/User.html#/s:5TDLib4UserV12profi.name: profilePhoto
Structs/User.html#/s:5TDLib4UserV12profi.abstract: Profile photo of the user; may be null

Structs/User.html#/s:5TDLib4UserV12outgo.name: outgoingLink
Structs/User.html#/s:5TDLib4UserV12outgo.abstract: Relationship from the current user to the other user

Structs/User.html#/s:5TDLib4UserV12incom.name: incomingLink
Structs/User.html#/s:5TDLib4UserV12incom.abstract: Relationship from the other user to the current user

Structs/User.html#/s:5TDLib4UserV17restr.name: restrictionReason
Structs/User.html#/s:5TDLib4UserV17restr.abstract: If non-empty, it contains the reason why access to this user must be restricted. The format of the string is {type}: {description}. -{type} contains the type of the restriction and at least one of the suffixes -all, -ios, -android, or -wp, which describe the platforms on which access should be restricted. (For example, terms-ios-android. {description} contains a human-readable description of the restriction, which can be shown to the user)

Structs/User.html#/s:5TDLib4UserV10haveA.name: haveAccess
Structs/User.html#/s:5TDLib4UserV10haveA.abstract: If false, the user is inaccessible, and the only information known about the user is inside this class. It can’t be passed to any method except GetUser

Structs/User.html#/s:5TDLib4UserV12langu.name: languageCode
Structs/User.html#/s:5TDLib4UserV12langu.abstract: IETF language tag of the user’s language; only available to bots

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: useTestDc
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: If set to true, the Telegram test environment will be used instead of the production environment

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: databaseDirectory
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: The path to the directory for the persistent database; if empty, the current working directory will be used

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: filesDirectory
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: The path to the directory for storing files; if empty, database_directory will be used

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: useFileDatabase
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: If set to true, information about downloaded and uploaded files will be saved between application restarts

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: useChatInfoDatabase
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: If set to true, the library will maintain a cache of users, basic groups, supergroups, channels and secret chats. Implies use_file_database

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: useMessageDatabase
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: If set to true, the library will maintain a cache of chats and messages. Implies use_chat_info_database

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: useSecretChats
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: If set to true, support for secret chats will be enabled

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: apiId
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: Application identifier for Telegram API access, which can be obtained at https://my.telegram.org

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: apiHash
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: Application identifier hash for Telegram API access, which can be obtained at https://my.telegram.org

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: systemLanguageCode
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: IETF language tag of the user’s operating system language; must be non-empty

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: deviceModel
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: Model of the device the application is being run on; must be non-empty

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: systemVersion
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: Version of the operating system the application is being run on; must be non-empty

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: enableStorageOptimizer
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: If set to true, old files will automatically be deleted

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: ignoreFileNames
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: If set to true, original file names will be ignored. Otherwise, downloaded files will be saved under names as close as possible to the original name

Structs/GetChatHistory.html#/s:5TDLib14G.name: fromMessageId
Structs/GetChatHistory.html#/s:5TDLib14G.abstract: Identifier of the message starting from which history must be fetched; use 0 to get results from the beginning (i.e., from oldest to newest)

Structs/GetChatHistory.html#/s:5TDLib14G.name: offset
Structs/GetChatHistory.html#/s:5TDLib14G.abstract: Specify 0 to get results from exactly the from_message_id or a negative offset to get the specified message and some newer messages

Structs/GetChatHistory.html#/s:5TDLib14G.name: limit
Structs/GetChatHistory.html#/s:5TDLib14G.abstract: The maximum number of messages to be returned; must be positive and can’t be greater than 100. If the offset is negative, the limit must be greater than -offset. Fewer messages may be returned than specified by the limit, even if the end of the message history has not been reached

Structs/GetChatHistory.html#/s:5TDLib14G.name: onlyLocal
Structs/GetChatHistory.html#/s:5TDLib14G.abstract: If true, returns only messages that are available locally without sending network requests

Structs/GetChatHistory.html#/s:5TDLib14G.name: init(chatId:fromMessageId:offset:limit:onlyLocal:)
Structs/GetChatHistory.html#/s:5TDLib14G.abstract: Returns messages in a chat. The messages are returned in a reverse chronological order (i.e., in order of decreasing message_id). -For optimal performance the number of returned messages is chosen by the library. This is an offline request if only_local is true

Structs/GetChats.html#/s:5TDLib8GetChats.name: limit
Structs/GetChats.html#/s:5TDLib8GetChats.abstract: The maximum number of chats to be returned. It is possible that fewer chats than the limit are returned even if the end of the list is not reached

Structs/GetChats.html#/s:5TDLib8GetChats.name: init(offsetOrder:offsetChatId:limit:)
Structs/GetChats.html#/s:5TDLib8GetChats.abstract: Returns an ordered list of chats. Chats are sorted by the pair (order, chat_id) in decreasing order. (For example, to get a list of chats from the beginning, the offset_order should be equal to 2^63 - 1). -For optimal performance the number of returned chats is chosen by the library.

Structs/Error.html#/s:5TDLib5ErrorV4code.name: code
Structs/Error.html#/s:5TDLib5ErrorV4code.abstract: Error code; subject to future changes. If the error code is 406, the error message must not be processed in any way and must not be displayed to the user

Structs/Error.html#/s:5TDLib5ErrorVACs5I.name: init(code:message:)
Structs/Error.html#/s:5TDLib5ErrorVACs5I.abstract: An object of this type can be returned on every function call, in case of an error

Structs/Error.html.name: Error
Structs/Error.html.abstract: An object of this type can be returned on every function call, in case of an error

Structs/GetChats.html.name: GetChats
Structs/GetChats.html.abstract: Returns an ordered list of chats. Chats are sorted by the pair (order, chat_id) in decreasing order. (For example, to get a list of chats from the beginning, the offset_order should be equal to 2^63 - 1). -For optimal performance the number of returned chats is chosen by the library.

Structs/GetChatHistory.html.name: GetChatHistory
Structs/GetChatHistory.html.abstract: Returns messages in a chat. The messages are returned in a reverse chronological order (i.e., in order of decreasing message_id). -For optimal performance the number of returned messages is chosen by the library. This is an offline request if only_local is true

Structs/Ok.html.name: Ok
Structs/Ok.html.abstract: An object of this type is returned on a successful function call for certain functions

Structs/AuthenticationCodeInfo.html.name: AuthenticationCodeInfo
Structs/AuthenticationCodeInfo.html.abstract: Information about the authentication code that was sent

Structs/PasswordRecoveryInfo.html.name: PasswordRecoveryInfo
Structs/PasswordRecoveryInfo.html.abstract: Contains information available to the user after requesting password recovery

Structs/RecoveryEmailAddress.html.name: RecoveryEmailAddress
Structs/RecoveryEmailAddress.html.abstract: Contains information about the current recovery email address

Structs/TemporaryPasswordState.html.name: TemporaryPasswordState
Structs/TemporaryPasswordState.html.abstract: Returns information about the availability of a temporary password, which can be used for payments

Structs/MaskPosition.html.name: MaskPosition
Structs/MaskPosition.html.abstract: Position on a photo where a mask should be placed

Structs/TextEntity.html.name: TextEntity
Structs/TextEntity.html.abstract: Represents a part of the text that needs to be formatted in some unusual way

Structs/Animation.html.name: Animation
Structs/Animation.html.abstract: Describes an animation file. The animation must be encoded in GIF or MPEG4 format

Structs/Audio.html.name: Audio
Structs/Audio.html.abstract: Describes an audio file. Audio is usually in MP3 format

Structs/VideoNote.html.name: VideoNote
Structs/VideoNote.html.abstract: Describes a video note. The video must be equal in width and height, cropped to a circle, and stored in MPEG4 format

Structs/VoiceNote.html.name: VoiceNote
Structs/VoiceNote.html.abstract: Describes a voice note. The voice note must be encoded with the Opus codec, and stored inside an OGG container. Voice notes can have only a single audio channel

Structs/BotInfo.html.name: BotInfo
Structs/BotInfo.html.abstract: Provides information about a bot and its supported commands

Structs/UserFullInfo.html.name: UserFullInfo
Structs/UserFullInfo.html.abstract: Contains full information about a user (except the full list of profile photos)

Structs/UserProfilePhotos.html.name: UserProfilePhotos
Structs/UserProfilePhotos.html.abstract: Contains part of the list of user photos

Structs/ChatMember.html.name: ChatMember
Structs/ChatMember.html.abstract: A user with information about joining/leaving a chat

Structs/BasicGroup.html.name: BasicGroup
Structs/BasicGroup.html.abstract: Represents a basic group of 0-200 users (must be upgraded to a supergroup to accommodate more than 200 users)

Structs/BasicGroupFullInfo.html.name: BasicGroupFullInfo
Structs/BasicGroupFullInfo.html.abstract: Contains full information about a basic group

Structs/Supergroup.html.name: Supergroup
Structs/Supergroup.html.abstract: Represents a supergroup or channel with zero or more members (subscribers in the case of channels). From the point of view of the system, a channel is a special kind of a supergroup: only administrators can post and see the list of members, and posts from all administrators use the name and photo of the channel instead of individual names and profile photos. Unlike supergroups, channels can have an unlimited number of subscribers

Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html.name: SupergroupFullInfo
Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html.abstract: Contains full information about a supergroup or channel

Structs/FoundMessages.html.name: FoundMessages
Structs/FoundMessages.html.abstract: Contains a list of messages found by a search

Structs/NotificationSettings.html.name: NotificationSettings
Structs/NotificationSettings.html.abstract: Contains information about notification settings for a chat or several chats

Structs/Chat.html.name: Chat
Structs/Chat.html.abstract: A chat. (Can be a private chat, basic group, supergroup, or secret chat)

Structs/ChatInviteLinkInfo.html.name: ChatInviteLinkInfo
Structs/ChatInviteLinkInfo.html.abstract: Contains information about a chat invite link

Structs/KeyboardButton.html.name: KeyboardButton
Structs/KeyboardButton.html.abstract: Represents a single button in a bot keyboard

Structs/InlineKeyboardButton.html.name: InlineKeyboardButton
Structs/InlineKeyboardButton.html.abstract: Represents a single button in an inline keyboard

Structs/WebPageInstantView.html.name: WebPageInstantView
Structs/WebPageInstantView.html.abstract: Describes an instant view page for a web page

Structs/LabeledPricePart.html.name: LabeledPricePart
Structs/LabeledPricePart.html.abstract: Portion of the price of a product (e.g., delivery cost, tax amount)

Structs/PaymentForm.html.name: PaymentForm
Structs/PaymentForm.html.abstract: Contains information about an invoice payment form

Structs/ValidatedOrderInfo.html.name: ValidatedOrderInfo
Structs/ValidatedOrderInfo.html.abstract: Contains a temporary identifier of validated order information, which is stored for one hour. Also contains the available shipping options

Structs/PaymentResult.html.name: PaymentResult
Structs/PaymentResult.html.abstract: Contains the result of a payment request

Structs/InputThumbnail.html.name: InputThumbnail
Structs/InputThumbnail.html.abstract: A thumbnail to be sent along with a file; should be in JPEG or WEBP format for stickers, and less than 200 kB in size

Structs/StickerEmojis.html.name: StickerEmojis
Structs/StickerEmojis.html.abstract: Represents a list of all emoji corresponding to a sticker in a sticker set. The list is only for informational purposes, because a sticker is always sent with a fixed emoji from the corresponding Sticker object

Structs/StickerSetInfo.html.name: StickerSetInfo
Structs/StickerSetInfo.html.abstract: Represents short information about a sticker set

Structs/ImportedContacts.html.name: ImportedContacts
Structs/ImportedContacts.html.abstract: Represents the result of an ImportContacts request

Structs/InlineQueryResults.html.name: InlineQueryResults
Structs/InlineQueryResults.html.abstract: Represents the results of the inline query. Use sendInlineQueryResultMessage to send the result of the query

Structs/CallbackQueryAnswer.html.name: CallbackQueryAnswer
Structs/CallbackQueryAnswer.html.abstract: Contains a bot’s answer to a callback query

Structs/CustomRequestResult.html.name: CustomRequestResult
Structs/CustomRequestResult.html.abstract: Contains the result of a custom request

Structs/GameHighScore.html.name: GameHighScore
Structs/GameHighScore.html.abstract: Contains one row of the game high score table

Structs/GameHighScores.html.name: GameHighScores
Structs/GameHighScores.html.abstract: Contains a list of game high scores

Structs/ChatEventLogFilters.html.name: ChatEventLogFilters
Structs/ChatEventLogFilters.html.abstract: Represents a set of filters used to obtain a chat event log

Structs/UserPrivacySettingRules.html.name: UserPrivacySettingRules
Structs/UserPrivacySettingRules.html.abstract: A list of privacy rules. Rules are matched in the specified order. The first matched rule defines the privacy setting for a given user. If no rule matches, the action is not allowed

Structs/AccountTtl.html.name: AccountTtl
Structs/AccountTtl.html.abstract: Contains information about the period of inactivity after which the current user’s account will automatically be deleted

Structs/Session.html.name: Session
Structs/Session.html.abstract: Contains information about one session in a Telegram application used by the current user

Structs/ConnectedWebsite.html.name: ConnectedWebsite
Structs/ConnectedWebsite.html.abstract: Contains information about one website the current user is logged in with Telegram

Structs/ConnectedWebsites.html.name: ConnectedWebsites
Structs/ConnectedWebsites.html.abstract: Contains a list of websites the current user is logged in with Telegram

Structs/ChatReportSpamState.html.name: ChatReportSpamState
Structs/ChatReportSpamState.html.abstract: Contains information about the availability of the Report spam action for a chat

Structs/PublicMessageLink.html.name: PublicMessageLink
Structs/PublicMessageLink.html.abstract: Contains a public HTTPS link to a message in a public supergroup or channel

Structs/StorageStatisticsByFileType.html.name: StorageStatisticsByFileType
Structs/StorageStatisticsByFileType.html.abstract: Contains the storage usage statistics for a specific file type

Structs/StorageStatisticsByChat.html.name: StorageStatisticsByChat
Structs/StorageStatisticsByChat.html.abstract: Contains the storage usage statistics for a specific chat

Structs/StorageStatistics.html.name: StorageStatistics
Structs/StorageStatistics.html.abstract: Contains the exact storage usage statistics split by chats and file type

Structs/StorageStatisticsFast.html.name: StorageStatisticsFast
Structs/StorageStatisticsFast.html.abstract: Contains approximate storage usage statistics, excluding files of unknown file type

Structs/NetworkStatistics.html.name: NetworkStatistics
Structs/NetworkStatistics.html.abstract: A full list of available network statistic entries

Structs/TMeUrl.html.name: TMeUrl
Structs/TMeUrl.html.abstract: Represents a URL linking to an internal Telegram entity

Structs/InputSticker.html.name: InputSticker
Structs/InputSticker.html.abstract: Describes a sticker that should be added to a sticker set

Structs/TestInt.html.name: TestInt
Structs/TestInt.html.abstract: A simple object containing a number; for testing only

Structs/TestString.html.name: TestString
Structs/TestString.html.abstract: A simple object containing a string; for testing only

Structs/TestBytes.html.name: TestBytes
Structs/TestBytes.html.abstract: A simple object containing a sequence of bytes; for testing only

Structs/TestVectorInt.html.name: TestVectorInt
Structs/TestVectorInt.html.abstract: A simple object containing a vector of numbers; for testing only

Structs/TestVectorIntObject.html.name: TestVectorIntObject
Structs/TestVectorIntObject.html.abstract: A simple object containing a vector of objects that hold a number; for testing only

Structs/TestVectorString.html.name: TestVectorString
Structs/TestVectorString.html.abstract: A simple object containing a vector of strings; for testing only

Structs/TestVectorStringObject.html.name: TestVectorStringObject
Structs/TestVectorStringObject.html.abstract: A simple object containing a vector of objects that hold a string; for testing only

Structs/GetAuthorizationState.html.name: GetAuthorizationState
Structs/GetAuthorizationState.html.abstract: Returns the current authorization state; this is an offline request. For informational purposes only. Use updateAuthorizationState instead to maintain the current authorization state

Structs/SetTdlibParameters.html.name: SetTdlibParameters
Structs/SetTdlibParameters.html.abstract: Sets the parameters for TDLib initialization. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitTdlibParameters

Structs/CheckDatabaseEncryptionKey.html.name: CheckDatabaseEncryptionKey
Structs/CheckDatabaseEncryptionKey.html.abstract: Checks the database encryption key for correctness. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitEncryptionKey

Structs/SetAuthenticationPhoneNumber.htm.name: SetAuthenticationPhoneNumber
Structs/SetAuthenticationPhoneNumber.htm.abstract: Sets the phone number of the user and sends an authentication code to the user. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPhoneNumber

Structs/ResendAuthenticationCode.html.name: ResendAuthenticationCode
Structs/ResendAuthenticationCode.html.abstract: Re-sends an authentication code to the user. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitCode and the next_code_type of the result is not null

Structs/CheckAuthenticationCode.html.name: CheckAuthenticationCode
Structs/CheckAuthenticationCode.html.abstract: Checks the authentication code. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitCode

Structs/CheckAuthenticationPassword.html.name: CheckAuthenticationPassword
Structs/CheckAuthenticationPassword.html.abstract: Checks the authentication password for correctness. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword

Structs/RequestAuthenticationPasswordRec.name: RequestAuthenticationPasswordRecovery
Structs/RequestAuthenticationPasswordRec.abstract: Requests to send a password recovery code to an email address that was previously set up. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword

Structs/RecoverAuthenticationPassword.ht.name: RecoverAuthenticationPassword
Structs/RecoverAuthenticationPassword.ht.abstract: Recovers the password with a password recovery code sent to an email address that was previously set up. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword

Structs/CheckAuthenticationBotToken.html.name: CheckAuthenticationBotToken
Structs/CheckAuthenticationBotToken.html.abstract: Checks the authentication token of a bot; to log in as a bot. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPhoneNumber. Can be used instead of setAuthenticationPhoneNumber and checkAuthenticationCode to log in

Structs/LogOut.html.name: LogOut
Structs/LogOut.html.abstract: Closes the TDLib instance after a proper logout. Requires an available network connection. All local data will be destroyed. After the logout completes, updateAuthorizationState with authorizationStateClosed will be sent

Structs/Close.html.name: Close
Structs/Close.html.abstract: Closes the TDLib instance. All databases will be flushed to disk and properly closed. After the close completes, updateAuthorizationState with authorizationStateClosed will be sent

Structs/Destroy.html.name: Destroy
Structs/Destroy.html.abstract: Closes the TDLib instance, destroying all local data without a proper logout. The current user session will remain in the list of all active sessions. All local data will be destroyed. After the destruction completes updateAuthorizationState with authorizationStateClosed will be sent

Structs/SetDatabaseEncryptionKey.html.name: SetDatabaseEncryptionKey
Structs/SetDatabaseEncryptionKey.html.abstract: Changes the database encryption key. Usually the encryption key is never changed and is stored in some OS keychain

Structs/SetPassword.html.name: SetPassword
Structs/SetPassword.html.abstract: Changes the password for the user. If a new recovery email address is specified, then the error EMAIL_UNCONFIRMED is returned and the password change will not be applied until the new recovery email address has been confirmed. The application should periodically call getPasswordState to check whether the new email address has been confirmed

Structs/GetRecoveryEmailAddress.html.name: GetRecoveryEmailAddress
Structs/GetRecoveryEmailAddress.html.abstract: Returns a recovery email address that was previously set up. This method can be used to verify a password provided by the user

Structs/SetRecoveryEmailAddress.html.name: SetRecoveryEmailAddress
Structs/SetRecoveryEmailAddress.html.abstract: Changes the recovery email address of the user. If a new recovery email address is specified, then the error EMAIL_UNCONFIRMED is returned and the email address will not be changed until the new email has been confirmed. The application should periodically call getPasswordState to check whether the email address has been confirmed. -If new_recovery_email_address is the same as the email address that is currently set up, this call succeeds immediately and aborts all other requests waiting for an email confirmation

Structs/RequestPasswordRecovery.html.name: RequestPasswordRecovery
Structs/RequestPasswordRecovery.html.abstract: Requests to send a password recovery code to an email address that was previously set up

Structs/RecoverPassword.html.name: RecoverPassword
Structs/RecoverPassword.html.abstract: Recovers the password using a recovery code sent to an email address that was previously set up

Structs/CreateTemporaryPassword.html.name: CreateTemporaryPassword
Structs/CreateTemporaryPassword.html.abstract: Creates a new temporary password for processing payments

Structs/GetTemporaryPasswordState.html.name: GetTemporaryPasswordState
Structs/GetTemporaryPasswordState.html.abstract: Returns information about the current temporary password

Structs/ProcessDcUpdate.html.name: ProcessDcUpdate
Structs/ProcessDcUpdate.html.abstract: Handles a DC_UPDATE push service notification. Can be called before authorization

Structs/GetUser.html.name: GetUser
Structs/GetUser.html.abstract: Returns information about a user by their identifier. This is an offline request if the current user is not a bot

Structs/GetUserFullInfo.html.name: GetUserFullInfo
Structs/GetUserFullInfo.html.abstract: Returns full information about a user by their identifier

Structs/GetBasicGroup.html.name: GetBasicGroup
Structs/GetBasicGroup.html.abstract: Returns information about a basic group by its identifier. This is an offline request if the current user is not a bot

Structs/GetBasicGroupFullInfo.html.name: GetBasicGroupFullInfo
Structs/GetBasicGroupFullInfo.html.abstract: Returns full information about a basic group by its identifier

Structs/GetSupergroup.html.name: GetSupergroup
Structs/GetSupergroup.html.abstract: Returns information about a supergroup or channel by its identifier. This is an offline request if the current user is not a bot

Structs/GetSupergroupFullInfo.html.name: GetSupergroupFullInfo
Structs/GetSupergroupFullInfo.html.abstract: Returns full information about a supergroup or channel by its identifier, cached for up to 1 minute

Structs/GetSecretChat.html.name: GetSecretChat
Structs/GetSecretChat.html.abstract: Returns information about a secret chat by its identifier. This is an offline request

Structs/GetChat.html.name: GetChat
Structs/GetChat.html.abstract: Returns information about a chat by its identifier, this is an offline request if the current user is not a bot

Structs/GetRepliedMessage.html.name: GetRepliedMessage
Structs/GetRepliedMessage.html.abstract: Returns information about a message that is replied by given message

Structs/GetChatPinnedMessage.html.name: GetChatPinnedMessage
Structs/GetChatPinnedMessage.html.abstract: Returns information about a pinned chat message

Structs/GetMessages.html.name: GetMessages
Structs/GetMessages.html.abstract: Returns information about messages. If a message is not found, returns null on the corresponding position of the result

Structs/GetFile.html.name: GetFile
Structs/GetFile.html.abstract: Returns information about a file; this is an offline request

Structs/GetRemoteFile.html.name: GetRemoteFile
Structs/GetRemoteFile.html.abstract: Returns information about a file by its remote ID; this is an offline request. Can be used to register a URL as a file for further uploading, or sending as a message

Structs/SearchPublicChat.html.name: SearchPublicChat
Structs/SearchPublicChat.html.abstract: Searches a public chat by its username. Currently only private chats, supergroups and channels can be public. Returns the chat if found; otherwise an error is returned

Structs/SearchPublicChats.html.name: SearchPublicChats
Structs/SearchPublicChats.html.abstract: Searches public chats by looking for specified query in their username and title. Currently only private chats, supergroups and channels can be public. Returns a meaningful number of results. Returns nothing if the length of the searched username prefix is less than 5. Excludes private chats with contacts and chats from the chat list from the results

Structs/SearchChats.html.name: SearchChats
Structs/SearchChats.html.abstract: Searches for the specified query in the title and username of already known chats, this is an offline request. Returns chats in the order seen in the chat list

Structs/SearchChatsOnServer.html.name: SearchChatsOnServer
Structs/SearchChatsOnServer.html.abstract: Searches for the specified query in the title and username of already known chats via request to the server. Returns chats in the order seen in the chat list

Structs/GetTopChats.html.name: GetTopChats
Structs/GetTopChats.html.abstract: Returns a list of frequently used chats. Supported only if the chat info database is enabled

Structs/RemoveTopChat.html.name: RemoveTopChat
Structs/RemoveTopChat.html.abstract: Removes a chat from the list of frequently used chats. Supported only if the chat info database is enabled

Structs/AddRecentlyFoundChat.html.name: AddRecentlyFoundChat
Structs/AddRecentlyFoundChat.html.abstract: Adds a chat to the list of recently found chats. The chat is added to the beginning of the list. If the chat is already in the list, it will be removed from the list first

Structs/RemoveRecentlyFoundChat.html.name: RemoveRecentlyFoundChat
Structs/RemoveRecentlyFoundChat.html.abstract: Removes a chat from the list of recently found chats

Structs/ClearRecentlyFoundChats.html.name: ClearRecentlyFoundChats
Structs/ClearRecentlyFoundChats.html.abstract: Clears the list of recently found chats

Structs/CheckChatUsername.html.name: CheckChatUsername
Structs/CheckChatUsername.html.abstract: Checks whether a username can be set for a chat

Structs/GetCreatedPublicChats.html.name: GetCreatedPublicChats
Structs/GetCreatedPublicChats.html.abstract: Returns a list of public chats created by the user

Structs/GetGroupsInCommon.html.name: GetGroupsInCommon
Structs/GetGroupsInCommon.html.abstract: Returns a list of common chats with a given user. Chats are sorted by their type and creation date

Structs/DeleteChatHistory.html.name: DeleteChatHistory
Structs/DeleteChatHistory.html.abstract: Deletes all messages in the chat only for the user. Cannot be used in channels and public supergroups

Structs/SearchChatMessages.html.name: SearchChatMessages
Structs/SearchChatMessages.html.abstract: Searches for messages with given words in the chat. Returns the results in reverse chronological order, i.e. in order of decreasing message_id. Cannot be used in secret chats with a non-empty query -(searchSecretMessages should be used instead), or without an enabled message database. For optimal performance the number of returned messages is chosen by the library

Structs/SearchMessages.html.name: SearchMessages
Structs/SearchMessages.html.abstract: Searches for messages in all chats except secret chats. Returns the results in reverse chronological order (i.e., in order of decreasing (date, chat_id, message_id)). -For optimal performance the number of returned messages is chosen by the library

Structs/SearchSecretMessages.html.name: SearchSecretMessages
Structs/SearchSecretMessages.html.abstract: Searches for messages in secret chats. Returns the results in reverse chronological order. For optimal performance the number of returned messages is chosen by the library

Structs/SearchCallMessages.html.name: SearchCallMessages
Structs/SearchCallMessages.html.abstract: Searches for call messages. Returns the results in reverse chronological order (i. e., in order of decreasing message_id). For optimal performance the number of returned messages is chosen by the library

Structs/SearchChatRecentLocationMessages.name: SearchChatRecentLocationMessages
Structs/SearchChatRecentLocationMessages.abstract: Returns information about the recent locations of chat members that were sent to the chat. Returns up to 1 location message per user

Structs/GetActiveLiveLocationMessages.ht.name: GetActiveLiveLocationMessages
Structs/GetActiveLiveLocationMessages.ht.abstract: Returns all active live locations that should be updated by the client. The list is persistent across application restarts only if the message database is used

Structs/GetChatMessageByDate.html.name: GetChatMessageByDate
Structs/GetChatMessageByDate.html.abstract: Returns the last message sent in a chat no later than the specified date

Structs/GetPublicMessageLink.html.name: GetPublicMessageLink
Structs/GetPublicMessageLink.html.abstract: Returns a public HTTPS link to a message. Available only for messages in public supergroups and channels

Structs/SendMessage.html.name: SendMessage
Structs/SendMessage.html.abstract: Sends a message. Returns the sent message

Structs/SendMessageAlbum.html.name: SendMessageAlbum
Structs/SendMessageAlbum.html.abstract: Sends messages grouped together into an album. Currently only photo and video messages can be grouped into an album. Returns sent messages

Structs/SendBotStartMessage.html.name: SendBotStartMessage
Structs/SendBotStartMessage.html.abstract: Invites a bot to a chat (if it is not yet a member) and sends it the /start command. Bots can’t be invited to a private chat other than the chat with the bot. Bots can’t be invited to channels (although they can be added as admins) and secret chats. Returns the sent message

Structs/SendInlineQueryResultMessage.htm.name: SendInlineQueryResultMessage
Structs/SendInlineQueryResultMessage.htm.abstract: Sends the result of an inline query as a message. Returns the sent message. Always clears a chat draft message

Structs/ForwardMessages.html.name: ForwardMessages
Structs/ForwardMessages.html.abstract: Forwards previously sent messages. Returns the forwarded messages in the same order as the message identifiers passed in message_ids. If a message can’t be forwarded, null will be returned instead of the message

Structs/SendChatSetTtlMessage.html.name: SendChatSetTtlMessage
Structs/SendChatSetTtlMessage.html.abstract: Changes the current TTL setting (sets a new self-destruct timer) in a secret chat and sends the corresponding message

Structs/SendChatScreenshotTakenNotificat.name: SendChatScreenshotTakenNotification
Structs/SendChatScreenshotTakenNotificat.abstract: Sends a notification about a screenshot taken in a chat. Supported only in private and secret chats

Structs/DeleteChatMessagesFromUser.html.name: DeleteChatMessagesFromUser
Structs/DeleteChatMessagesFromUser.html.abstract: Deletes all messages sent by the specified user to a chat. Supported only in supergroups; requires can_delete_messages administrator privileges

Structs/EditMessageText.html.name: EditMessageText
Structs/EditMessageText.html.abstract: Edits the text of a message (or a text of a game message). Non-bot users can edit messages for a limited period of time. Returns the edited message after the edit is completed on the server side

Structs/EditMessageLiveLocation.html.name: EditMessageLiveLocation
Structs/EditMessageLiveLocation.html.abstract: Edits the message content of a live location. Messages can be edited for a limited period of time specified in the live location. Returns the edited message after the edit is completed server-side

Structs/EditMessageCaption.html.name: EditMessageCaption
Structs/EditMessageCaption.html.abstract: Edits the message content caption. Non-bots can edit messages for a limited period of time. Returns the edited message after the edit is completed server-side

Structs/EditMessageReplyMarkup.html.name: EditMessageReplyMarkup
Structs/EditMessageReplyMarkup.html.abstract: Edits the message reply markup; for bots only. Returns the edited message after the edit is completed server-side

Structs/EditInlineMessageText.html.name: EditInlineMessageText
Structs/EditInlineMessageText.html.abstract: Edits the text of an inline text or game message sent via a bot; for bots only

Structs/EditInlineMessageLiveLocation.ht.name: EditInlineMessageLiveLocation
Structs/EditInlineMessageLiveLocation.ht.abstract: Edits the content of a live location in an inline message sent via a bot; for bots only

Structs/EditInlineMessageCaption.html.name: EditInlineMessageCaption
Structs/EditInlineMessageCaption.html.abstract: Edits the caption of an inline message sent via a bot; for bots only

Structs/EditInlineMessageReplyMarkup.htm.name: EditInlineMessageReplyMarkup
Structs/EditInlineMessageReplyMarkup.htm.abstract: Edits the reply markup of an inline message sent via a bot; for bots only

Structs/GetTextEntities.html.name: GetTextEntities
Structs/GetTextEntities.html.abstract: Returns all entities (mentions, hashtags, cashtags, bot commands, URLs, and email addresses) contained in the text. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/ParseTextEntities.html.name: ParseTextEntities
Structs/ParseTextEntities.html.abstract: Parses Bold, Italic, Code, Pre, PreCode and TextUrl entities contained in the text. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/GetFileMimeType.html.name: GetFileMimeType
Structs/GetFileMimeType.html.abstract: Returns the MIME type of a file, guessed by its extension. Returns an empty string on failure. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/GetFileExtension.html.name: GetFileExtension
Structs/GetFileExtension.html.abstract: Returns the extension of a file, guessed by its MIME type. Returns an empty string on failure. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/GetInlineQueryResults.html.name: GetInlineQueryResults
Structs/GetInlineQueryResults.html.abstract: Sends an inline query to a bot and returns its results. Returns an error with code 502 if the bot fails to answer the query before the query timeout expires

Structs/AnswerInlineQuery.html.name: AnswerInlineQuery
Structs/AnswerInlineQuery.html.abstract: Sets the result of an inline query; for bots only

Structs/GetCallbackQueryAnswer.html.name: GetCallbackQueryAnswer
Structs/GetCallbackQueryAnswer.html.abstract: Sends a callback query to a bot and returns an answer. Returns an error with code 502 if the bot fails to answer the query before the query timeout expires

Structs/AnswerCallbackQuery.html.name: AnswerCallbackQuery
Structs/AnswerCallbackQuery.html.abstract: Sets the result of a callback query; for bots only

Structs/AnswerShippingQuery.html.name: AnswerShippingQuery
Structs/AnswerShippingQuery.html.abstract: Sets the result of a shipping query; for bots only

Structs/AnswerPreCheckoutQuery.html.name: AnswerPreCheckoutQuery
Structs/AnswerPreCheckoutQuery.html.abstract: Sets the result of a pre-checkout query; for bots only

Structs/SetGameScore.html.name: SetGameScore
Structs/SetGameScore.html.abstract: Updates the game score of the specified user in the game; for bots only

Structs/SetInlineGameScore.html.name: SetInlineGameScore
Structs/SetInlineGameScore.html.abstract: Updates the game score of the specified user in a game; for bots only

Structs/GetGameHighScores.html.name: GetGameHighScores
Structs/GetGameHighScores.html.abstract: Returns the high scores for a game and some part of the high score table in the range of the specified user; for bots only

Structs/GetInlineGameHighScores.html.name: GetInlineGameHighScores
Structs/GetInlineGameHighScores.html.abstract: Returns game high scores and some part of the high score table in the range of the specified user; for bots only

Structs/DeleteChatReplyMarkup.html.name: DeleteChatReplyMarkup
Structs/DeleteChatReplyMarkup.html.abstract: Deletes the default reply markup from a chat. Must be called after a one-time keyboard or a ForceReply reply markup has been used. UpdateChatReplyMarkup will be sent if the reply markup will be changed

Structs/SendChatAction.html.name: SendChatAction
Structs/SendChatAction.html.abstract: Sends a notification about user activity in a chat

Structs/OpenChat.html.name: OpenChat
Structs/OpenChat.html.abstract: This method should be called if the chat is opened by the user. Many useful activities depend on the chat being opened or closed (e.g., in supergroups and channels all updates are received only for opened chats)

Structs/CloseChat.html.name: CloseChat
Structs/CloseChat.html.abstract: This method should be called if the chat is closed by the user. Many useful activities depend on the chat being opened or closed

Structs/ViewMessages.html.name: ViewMessages
Structs/ViewMessages.html.abstract: This method should be called if messages are being viewed by the user. Many useful activities depend on whether the messages are currently being viewed or not (e.g., marking messages as read, incrementing a view counter, updating a view counter, removing deleted messages in supergroups and channels)

Structs/OpenMessageContent.html.name: OpenMessageContent
Structs/OpenMessageContent.html.abstract: This method should be called if the message content has been opened (e.g., the user has opened a photo, video, document, location or venue, or has listened to an audio file or voice note message). An updateMessageContentOpened update will be generated if something has changed

Structs/ReadAllChatMentions.html.name: ReadAllChatMentions
Structs/ReadAllChatMentions.html.abstract: Marks all mentions in a chat as read

Structs/CreatePrivateChat.html.name: CreatePrivateChat
Structs/CreatePrivateChat.html.abstract: Returns an existing chat corresponding to a given user

Structs/CreateBasicGroupChat.html.name: CreateBasicGroupChat
Structs/CreateBasicGroupChat.html.abstract: Returns an existing chat corresponding to a known basic group

Structs/CreateSupergroupChat.html.name: CreateSupergroupChat
Structs/CreateSupergroupChat.html.abstract: Returns an existing chat corresponding to a known supergroup or channel

Structs/CreateSecretChat.html.name: CreateSecretChat
Structs/CreateSecretChat.html.abstract: Returns an existing chat corresponding to a known secret chat

Structs/CreateNewBasicGroupChat.html.name: CreateNewBasicGroupChat
Structs/CreateNewBasicGroupChat.html.abstract: Creates a new basic group and sends a corresponding messageBasicGroupChatCreate. Returns the newly created chat

Structs/CreateNewSupergroupChat.html.name: CreateNewSupergroupChat
Structs/CreateNewSupergroupChat.html.abstract: Creates a new supergroup or channel and sends a corresponding messageSupergroupChatCreate. Returns the newly created chat

Structs/CreateNewSecretChat.html.name: CreateNewSecretChat
Structs/CreateNewSecretChat.html.abstract: Creates a new secret chat. Returns the newly created chat

Structs/UpgradeBasicGroupChatToSupergrou.name: UpgradeBasicGroupChatToSupergroupChat
Structs/UpgradeBasicGroupChatToSupergrou.abstract: Creates a new supergroup from an existing basic group and sends a corresponding messageChatUpgradeTo and messageChatUpgradeFrom. Deactivates the original basic group

Structs/SetChatTitle.html.name: SetChatTitle
Structs/SetChatTitle.html.abstract: Changes the chat title. Supported only for basic groups, supergroups and channels. Requires administrator rights in basic groups and the appropriate administrator rights in supergroups and channels. The title will not be changed until the request to the server has been completed

Structs/SetChatPhoto.html.name: SetChatPhoto
Structs/SetChatPhoto.html.abstract: Changes the photo of a chat. Supported only for basic groups, supergroups and channels. Requires administrator rights in basic groups and the appropriate administrator rights in supergroups and channels. The photo will not be changed before request to the server has been completed

Structs/SetChatDraftMessage.html.name: SetChatDraftMessage
Structs/SetChatDraftMessage.html.abstract: Changes the draft message in a chat

Structs/ToggleChatIsPinned.html.name: ToggleChatIsPinned
Structs/ToggleChatIsPinned.html.abstract: Changes the pinned state of a chat. You can pin up to GetOption(pinned_chat_count_max) non-secret chats and the same number of secret chats

Structs/SetChatClientData.html.name: SetChatClientData
Structs/SetChatClientData.html.abstract: Changes client data associated with a chat

Structs/AddChatMember.html.name: AddChatMember
Structs/AddChatMember.html.abstract: Adds a new member to a chat. Members can’t be added to private or secret chats. Members will not be added until the chat state has been synchronized with the server

Structs/AddChatMembers.html.name: AddChatMembers
Structs/AddChatMembers.html.abstract: Adds multiple new members to a chat. Currently this option is only available for supergroups and channels. This option can’t be used to join a chat. Members can’t be added to a channel if it has more than 200 members. Members will not be added until the chat state has been synchronized with the server

Structs/SetChatMemberStatus.html.name: SetChatMemberStatus
Structs/SetChatMemberStatus.html.abstract: Changes the status of a chat member, needs appropriate privileges. This function is currently not suitable for adding new members to the chat; instead, use addChatMember. The chat member status will not be changed until it has been synchronized with the server

Structs/GetChatMember.html.name: GetChatMember
Structs/GetChatMember.html.abstract: Returns information about a single member of a chat

Structs/SearchChatMembers.html.name: SearchChatMembers
Structs/SearchChatMembers.html.abstract: Searches for a specified query in the first name, last name and username of the members of a specified chat. Requires administrator rights in channels

Structs/GetChatAdministrators.html.name: GetChatAdministrators
Structs/GetChatAdministrators.html.abstract: Returns a list of users who are administrators of the chat

Structs/DownloadFile.html.name: DownloadFile
Structs/DownloadFile.html.abstract: Asynchronously downloads a file from the cloud. updateFile will be used to notify about the download progress and successful completion of the download. Returns file state just after the download has been started

Structs/CancelDownloadFile.html.name: CancelDownloadFile
Structs/CancelDownloadFile.html.abstract: Stops the downloading of a file. If a file has already been downloaded, does nothing

Structs/UploadFile.html.name: UploadFile
Structs/UploadFile.html.abstract: Asynchronously uploads a file to the cloud without sending it in a message. updateFile will be used to notify about upload progress and successful completion of the upload. The file will not have a persistent remote identifier until it will be sent in a message

Structs/CancelUploadFile.html.name: CancelUploadFile
Structs/CancelUploadFile.html.abstract: Stops the uploading of a file. Supported only for files uploaded by using uploadFile. For other files the behavior is undefined

Structs/SetFileGenerationProgress.html.name: SetFileGenerationProgress
Structs/SetFileGenerationProgress.html.abstract: The next part of a file was generated

Structs/DeleteFile.html.name: DeleteFile
Structs/DeleteFile.html.abstract: Deletes a file from the TDLib file cache

Structs/GenerateChatInviteLink.html.name: GenerateChatInviteLink
Structs/GenerateChatInviteLink.html.abstract: Generates a new invite link for a chat; the previously generated link is revoked. Available for basic groups, supergroups, and channels. In basic groups this can be called only by the group’s creator; in supergroups and channels this requires appropriate administrator rights

Structs/CheckChatInviteLink.html.name: CheckChatInviteLink
Structs/CheckChatInviteLink.html.abstract: Checks the validity of an invite link for a chat and returns information about the corresponding chat

Structs/JoinChatByInviteLink.html.name: JoinChatByInviteLink
Structs/JoinChatByInviteLink.html.abstract: Uses an invite link to add the current user to the chat if possible. The new member will not be added until the chat state has been synchronized with the server

Structs/GetBlockedUsers.html.name: GetBlockedUsers
Structs/GetBlockedUsers.html.abstract: Returns users that were blocked by the current user

Structs/ImportContacts.html.name: ImportContacts
Structs/ImportContacts.html.abstract: Adds new contacts or edits existing contacts; contacts’ user identifiers are ignored

Structs/SearchContacts.html.name: SearchContacts
Structs/SearchContacts.html.abstract: Searches for the specified query in the first names, last names and usernames of the known user contacts

Structs/GetImportedContactCount.html.name: GetImportedContactCount
Structs/GetImportedContactCount.html.abstract: Returns the total number of imported contacts

Structs/ChangeImportedContacts.html.name: ChangeImportedContacts
Structs/ChangeImportedContacts.html.abstract: Changes imported contacts using the list of current user contacts saved on the device. Imports newly added contacts and, if at least the file database is enabled, deletes recently deleted contacts. -Query result depends on the result of the previous query, so only one query is possible at the same time

Structs/GetUserProfilePhotos.html.name: GetUserProfilePhotos
Structs/GetUserProfilePhotos.html.abstract: Returns the profile photos of a user. The result of this query may be outdated: some photos might have been deleted already

Structs/GetStickers.html.name: GetStickers
Structs/GetStickers.html.abstract: Returns stickers from the installed sticker sets that correspond to a given emoji. If the emoji is not empty, favorite and recently used stickers may also be returned

Structs/SearchStickers.html.name: SearchStickers
Structs/SearchStickers.html.abstract: Searches for stickers from public sticker sets that correspond to a given emoji

Structs/GetInstalledStickerSets.html.name: GetInstalledStickerSets
Structs/GetInstalledStickerSets.html.abstract: Returns a list of installed sticker sets

Structs/GetArchivedStickerSets.html.name: GetArchivedStickerSets
Structs/GetArchivedStickerSets.html.abstract: Returns a list of archived sticker sets

Structs/GetTrendingStickerSets.html.name: GetTrendingStickerSets
Structs/GetTrendingStickerSets.html.abstract: Returns a list of trending sticker sets

Structs/GetAttachedStickerSets.html.name: GetAttachedStickerSets
Structs/GetAttachedStickerSets.html.abstract: Returns a list of sticker sets attached to a file. Currently only photos and videos can have attached sticker sets

Structs/GetStickerSet.html.name: GetStickerSet
Structs/GetStickerSet.html.abstract: Returns information about a sticker set by its identifier

Structs/SearchStickerSet.html.name: SearchStickerSet
Structs/SearchStickerSet.html.abstract: Searches for a sticker set by its name

Structs/SearchInstalledStickerSets.html.name: SearchInstalledStickerSets
Structs/SearchInstalledStickerSets.html.abstract: Searches for installed sticker sets by looking for specified query in their title and name

Structs/SearchStickerSets.html.name: SearchStickerSets
Structs/SearchStickerSets.html.abstract: Searches for ordinary sticker sets by looking for specified query in their title and name. Excludes installed sticker sets from the results

Structs/ViewTrendingStickerSets.html.name: ViewTrendingStickerSets
Structs/ViewTrendingStickerSets.html.abstract: Informs the server that some trending sticker sets have been viewed by the user

Structs/ReorderInstalledStickerSets.html.name: ReorderInstalledStickerSets
Structs/ReorderInstalledStickerSets.html.abstract: Changes the order of installed sticker sets

Structs/GetRecentStickers.html.name: GetRecentStickers
Structs/GetRecentStickers.html.abstract: Returns a list of recently used stickers

Structs/AddRecentSticker.html.name: AddRecentSticker
Structs/AddRecentSticker.html.abstract: Manually adds a new sticker to the list of recently used stickers. The new sticker is added to the top of the list. If the sticker was already in the list, it is removed from the list first. Only stickers belonging to a sticker set can be added to this list

Structs/RemoveRecentSticker.html.name: RemoveRecentSticker
Structs/RemoveRecentSticker.html.abstract: Removes a sticker from the list of recently used stickers

Structs/ClearRecentStickers.html.name: ClearRecentStickers
Structs/ClearRecentStickers.html.abstract: Clears the list of recently used stickers

Structs/AddFavoriteSticker.html.name: AddFavoriteSticker
Structs/AddFavoriteSticker.html.abstract: Adds a new sticker to the list of favorite stickers. The new sticker is added to the top of the list. If the sticker was already in the list, it is removed from the list first. Only stickers belonging to a sticker set can be added to this list

Structs/RemoveFavoriteSticker.html.name: RemoveFavoriteSticker
Structs/RemoveFavoriteSticker.html.abstract: Removes a sticker from the list of favorite stickers

Structs/AddSavedAnimation.html.name: AddSavedAnimation
Structs/AddSavedAnimation.html.abstract: Manually adds a new animation to the list of saved animations. The new animation is added to the beginning of the list. If the animation was already in the list, it is removed first. Only non-secret video animations with MIME type video/mp4 can be added to the list

Structs/RemoveSavedAnimation.html.name: RemoveSavedAnimation
Structs/RemoveSavedAnimation.html.abstract: Removes an animation from the list of saved animations

Structs/GetRecentInlineBots.html.name: GetRecentInlineBots
Structs/GetRecentInlineBots.html.abstract: Returns up to 20 recently used inline bots in the order of their last usage

Structs/SearchHashtags.html.name: SearchHashtags
Structs/SearchHashtags.html.abstract: Searches for recently used hashtags by their prefix

Structs/RemoveRecentHashtag.html.name: RemoveRecentHashtag
Structs/RemoveRecentHashtag.html.abstract: Removes a hashtag from the list of recently used hashtags

Structs/GetWebPagePreview.html.name: GetWebPagePreview
Structs/GetWebPagePreview.html.abstract: Returns a web page preview by the text of the message. Do not call this function too often. Returns a 404 error if the web page has no preview

Structs/GetWebPageInstantView.html.name: GetWebPageInstantView
Structs/GetWebPageInstantView.html.abstract: Returns an instant view version of a web page if available. Returns a 404 error if the web page has no instant view page

Structs/GetNotificationSettings.html.name: GetNotificationSettings
Structs/GetNotificationSettings.html.abstract: Returns the notification settings for a given scope

Structs/SetNotificationSettings.html.name: SetNotificationSettings
Structs/SetNotificationSettings.html.abstract: Changes notification settings for a given scope

Structs/ResetAllNotificationSettings.htm.name: ResetAllNotificationSettings
Structs/ResetAllNotificationSettings.htm.abstract: Resets all notification settings to their default values. By default, the only muted chats are supergroups, the sound is set to default and message previews are shown

Structs/SetProfilePhoto.html.name: SetProfilePhoto
Structs/SetProfilePhoto.html.abstract: Uploads a new profile photo for the current user. If something changes, updateUser will be sent

Structs/DeleteProfilePhoto.html.name: DeleteProfilePhoto
Structs/DeleteProfilePhoto.html.abstract: Deletes a profile photo. If something changes, updateUser will be sent

Structs/SetName.html.name: SetName
Structs/SetName.html.abstract: Changes the first and last name of the current user. If something changes, updateUser will be sent

Structs/SetBio.html.name: SetBio
Structs/SetBio.html.abstract: Changes the bio of the current user

Structs/SetUsername.html.name: SetUsername
Structs/SetUsername.html.abstract: Changes the username of the current user. If something changes, updateUser will be sent

Structs/ChangePhoneNumber.html.name: ChangePhoneNumber
Structs/ChangePhoneNumber.html.abstract: Changes the phone number of the user and sends an authentication code to the user’s new phone number. On success, returns information about the sent code

Structs/ResendChangePhoneNumberCode.html.name: ResendChangePhoneNumberCode
Structs/ResendChangePhoneNumberCode.html.abstract: Re-sends the authentication code sent to confirm a new phone number for the user. Works only if the previously received authenticationCodeInfo next_code_type was not null

Structs/CheckChangePhoneNumberCode.html.name: CheckChangePhoneNumberCode
Structs/CheckChangePhoneNumberCode.html.abstract: Checks the authentication code sent to confirm a new phone number of the user

Structs/GetActiveSessions.html.name: GetActiveSessions
Structs/GetActiveSessions.html.abstract: Returns all active sessions of the current user

Structs/TerminateSession.html.name: TerminateSession
Structs/TerminateSession.html.abstract: Terminates a session of the current user

Structs/TerminateAllOtherSessions.html.name: TerminateAllOtherSessions
Structs/TerminateAllOtherSessions.html.abstract: Terminates all other sessions of the current user

Structs/GetConnectedWebsites.html.name: GetConnectedWebsites
Structs/GetConnectedWebsites.html.abstract: Returns all website where the current user used Telegram to log in

Structs/DisconnectWebsite.html.name: DisconnectWebsite
Structs/DisconnectWebsite.html.abstract: Disconnects website from the current user’s Telegram account

Structs/DisconnectAllWebsites.html.name: DisconnectAllWebsites
Structs/DisconnectAllWebsites.html.abstract: Disconnects all websites from the current user’s Telegram account

Structs/ToggleBasicGroupAdministrators.h.name: ToggleBasicGroupAdministrators
Structs/ToggleBasicGroupAdministrators.h.abstract: Toggles the All members are admins setting in basic groups; requires creator privileges in the group

Structs/SetSupergroupUsername.html.name: SetSupergroupUsername
Structs/SetSupergroupUsername.html.abstract: Changes the username of a supergroup or channel, requires creator privileges in the supergroup or channel

Structs/SetSupergroupStickerSet.html.name: SetSupergroupStickerSet
Structs/SetSupergroupStickerSet.html.abstract: Changes the sticker set of a supergroup; requires appropriate rights in the supergroup

Structs/ToggleSupergroupInvites.html.name: ToggleSupergroupInvites
Structs/ToggleSupergroupInvites.html.abstract: Toggles whether all members of a supergroup can add new members; requires appropriate administrator rights in the supergroup.

Structs/ToggleSupergroupSignMessages.htm.name: ToggleSupergroupSignMessages
Structs/ToggleSupergroupSignMessages.htm.abstract: Toggles sender signatures messages sent in a channel; requires appropriate administrator rights in the channel.

Structs/ToggleSupergroupIsAllHistoryAvai.name: ToggleSupergroupIsAllHistoryAvailable
Structs/ToggleSupergroupIsAllHistoryAvai.abstract: Toggles whether the message history of a supergroup is available to new members; requires appropriate administrator rights in the supergroup.

Structs/SetSupergroupDescription.html.name: SetSupergroupDescription
Structs/SetSupergroupDescription.html.abstract: Changes information about a supergroup or channel; requires appropriate administrator rights

Structs/PinSupergroupMessage.html.name: PinSupergroupMessage
Structs/PinSupergroupMessage.html.abstract: Pins a message in a supergroup or channel; requires appropriate administrator rights in the supergroup or channel

Structs/UnpinSupergroupMessage.html.name: UnpinSupergroupMessage
Structs/UnpinSupergroupMessage.html.abstract: Removes the pinned message from a supergroup or channel; requires appropriate administrator rights in the supergroup or channel

Structs/ReportSupergroupSpam.html.name: ReportSupergroupSpam
Structs/ReportSupergroupSpam.html.abstract: Reports some messages from a user in a supergroup as spam

Structs/GetSupergroupMembers.html.name: GetSupergroupMembers
Structs/GetSupergroupMembers.html.abstract: Returns information about members or banned users in a supergroup or channel. Can be used only if SupergroupFullInfo.can_get_members == true; additionally, administrator privileges may be required for some filters

Structs/DeleteSupergroup.html.name: DeleteSupergroup
Structs/DeleteSupergroup.html.abstract: Deletes a supergroup or channel along with all messages in the corresponding chat. This will release the supergroup or channel username and remove all members; requires creator privileges in the supergroup or channel. Chats with more than 1000 members can’t be deleted using this method

Structs/CloseSecretChat.html.name: CloseSecretChat
Structs/CloseSecretChat.html.abstract: Closes a secret chat, effectively transfering its state to secretChatStateClosed

Structs/GetChatEventLog.html.name: GetChatEventLog
Structs/GetChatEventLog.html.abstract: Returns a list of service actions taken by chat members and administrators in the last 48 hours. Available only in supergroups and channels. Requires administrator rights. Returns results in reverse chronological order (i. e., in order of decreasing event_id)

Structs/GetPaymentForm.html.name: GetPaymentForm
Structs/GetPaymentForm.html.abstract: Returns an invoice payment form. This method should be called when the user presses inlineKeyboardButtonBuy

Structs/ValidateOrderInfo.html.name: ValidateOrderInfo
Structs/ValidateOrderInfo.html.abstract: Validates the order information provided by a user and returns the available shipping options for a flexible invoice

Structs/SendPaymentForm.html.name: SendPaymentForm
Structs/SendPaymentForm.html.abstract: Sends a filled-out payment form to the bot for final verification

Structs/DeleteSavedCredentials.html.name: DeleteSavedCredentials
Structs/DeleteSavedCredentials.html.abstract: Deletes saved credentials for all payment provider bots

Structs/GetSupportUser.html.name: GetSupportUser
Structs/GetSupportUser.html.abstract: Returns a user that can be contacted to get support

Structs/RegisterDevice.html.name: RegisterDevice
Structs/RegisterDevice.html.abstract: Registers the currently used device for receiving push notifications

Structs/GetRecentlyVisitedTMeUrls.html.name: GetRecentlyVisitedTMeUrls
Structs/GetRecentlyVisitedTMeUrls.html.abstract: Returns t.me URLs recently visited by a newly registered user

Structs/GetOption.html.name: GetOption
Structs/GetOption.html.abstract: Returns the value of an option by its name. (Check the list of available options on https://core.telegram.org/tdlib/options.) Can be called before authorization

Structs/SetOption.html.name: SetOption
Structs/SetOption.html.abstract: Sets the value of an option. (Check the list of available options on https://core.telegram.org/tdlib/options.) Only writable options can be set. Can be called before authorization

Structs/SetAccountTtl.html.name: SetAccountTtl
Structs/SetAccountTtl.html.abstract: Changes the period of inactivity after which the account of the current user will automatically be deleted

Structs/GetAccountTtl.html.name: GetAccountTtl
Structs/GetAccountTtl.html.abstract: Returns the period of inactivity after which the account of the current user will automatically be deleted

Structs/DeleteAccount.html.name: DeleteAccount
Structs/DeleteAccount.html.abstract: Deletes the account of the current user, deleting all information associated with the user from the server. The phone number of the account can be used to create a new account

Structs/GetChatReportSpamState.html.name: GetChatReportSpamState
Structs/GetChatReportSpamState.html.abstract: Returns information on whether the current chat can be reported as spam

Structs/ChangeChatReportSpamState.html.name: ChangeChatReportSpamState
Structs/ChangeChatReportSpamState.html.abstract: Used to let the server know whether a chat is spam or not. Can be used only if ChatReportSpamState.can_report_spam is true. After this request, ChatReportSpamState.can_report_spam becomes false forever

Structs/ReportChat.html.name: ReportChat
Structs/ReportChat.html.abstract: Reports a chat to the Telegram moderators. Supported only for supergroups, channels, or private chats with bots, since other chats can’t be checked by moderators

Structs/OptimizeStorage.html.name: OptimizeStorage
Structs/OptimizeStorage.html.abstract: Optimizes storage usage, i.e. deletes some files and returns new storage usage statistics. Secret thumbnails can’t be deleted

Structs/SetNetworkType.html.name: SetNetworkType
Structs/SetNetworkType.html.abstract: Sets the current network type. Can be called before authorization. Calling this method forces all network connections to reopen, mitigating the delay in switching between different networks, so it should be called whenever the network is changed, even if the network type remains the same. -Network type is used to check whether the library can use the network at all and also for collecting detailed network data usage statistics

Structs/GetNetworkStatistics.html.name: GetNetworkStatistics
Structs/GetNetworkStatistics.html.abstract: Returns network data usage statistics. Can be called before authorization

Structs/AddNetworkStatistics.html.name: AddNetworkStatistics
Structs/AddNetworkStatistics.html.abstract: Adds the specified data to data usage statistics. Can be called before authorization

Structs/ResetNetworkStatistics.html.name: ResetNetworkStatistics
Structs/ResetNetworkStatistics.html.abstract: Resets all network data usage statistics to zero. Can be called before authorization

Structs/SetBotUpdatesStatus.html.name: SetBotUpdatesStatus
Structs/SetBotUpdatesStatus.html.abstract: Informs the server about the number of pending bot updates if they haven’t been processed for a long time; for bots only

Structs/UploadStickerFile.html.name: UploadStickerFile
Structs/UploadStickerFile.html.abstract: Uploads a PNG image with a sticker; for bots only; returns the uploaded file

Structs/CreateNewStickerSet.html.name: CreateNewStickerSet
Structs/CreateNewStickerSet.html.abstract: Creates a new sticker set; for bots only. Returns the newly created sticker set

Structs/AddStickerToSet.html.name: AddStickerToSet
Structs/AddStickerToSet.html.abstract: Adds a new sticker to a set; for bots only. Returns the sticker set

Structs/SetStickerPositionInSet.html.name: SetStickerPositionInSet
Structs/SetStickerPositionInSet.html.abstract: Changes the position of a sticker in the set to which it belongs; for bots only. The sticker set must have been created by the bot

Structs/RemoveStickerFromSet.html.name: RemoveStickerFromSet
Structs/RemoveStickerFromSet.html.abstract: Removes a sticker from the set to which it belongs; for bots only. The sticker set must have been created by the bot

Structs/SendCustomRequest.html.name: SendCustomRequest
Structs/SendCustomRequest.html.abstract: Sends a custom request; for bots only

Structs/AnswerCustomQuery.html.name: AnswerCustomQuery
Structs/AnswerCustomQuery.html.abstract: Answers a custom query; for bots only

Structs/SetAlarm.html.name: SetAlarm
Structs/SetAlarm.html.abstract: Succeeds after a specified amount of time has passed. Can be called before authorization

Structs/GetCountryCode.html.name: GetCountryCode
Structs/GetCountryCode.html.abstract: Uses current user IP to found his country. Returns two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code. Can be called before authorization

Structs/GetInviteText.html.name: GetInviteText
Structs/GetInviteText.html.abstract: Returns the default text for invitation messages to be used as a placeholder when the current user invites friends to Telegram

Structs/GetTermsOfService.html.name: GetTermsOfService
Structs/GetTermsOfService.html.abstract: Returns the terms of service. Can be called before authorization

Structs/SetProxy.html.name: SetProxy
Structs/SetProxy.html.abstract: Sets the proxy server for network requests. Can be called before authorization

Structs/GetProxy.html.name: GetProxy
Structs/GetProxy.html.abstract: Returns the proxy that is currently set up. Can be called before authorization

Structs/TestCallString.html.name: TestCallString
Structs/TestCallString.html.abstract: Returns the received string; for testing only

Structs/TestCallBytes.html.name: TestCallBytes
Structs/TestCallBytes.html.abstract: Returns the received bytes; for testing only

Structs/TestCallVectorInt.html.name: TestCallVectorInt
Structs/TestCallVectorInt.html.abstract: Returns the received vector of numbers; for testing only

Structs/TestCallVectorIntObject.html.name: TestCallVectorIntObject
Structs/TestCallVectorIntObject.html.abstract: Returns the received vector of objects containing a number; for testing only

Structs/TestCallVectorString.html.name: TestCallVectorString
Structs/TestCallVectorString.html.abstract: For testing only request. Returns the received vector of strings; for testing only

Structs/TestCallVectorStringObject.html.name: TestCallVectorStringObject
Structs/TestCallVectorStringObject.html.abstract: Returns the received vector of objects containing a string; for testing only

Structs/TestSquareInt.html.name: TestSquareInt
Structs/TestSquareInt.html.abstract: Returns the squared received number; for testing only

Structs/TestNetwork.html.name: TestNetwork
Structs/TestNetwork.html.abstract: Sends a simple network request to the Telegram servers; for testing only

Structs/TestGetDifference.html.name: TestGetDifference
Structs/TestGetDifference.html.abstract: Forces an updates.getDifference call to the Telegram servers; for testing only

Structs/TestUseUpdate.html.name: TestUseUpdate
Structs/TestUseUpdate.html.abstract: Does nothing and ensures that the Update object is used; for testing only

Structs/TestUseError.html.name: TestUseError
Structs/TestUseError.html.abstract: Does nothing and ensures that the Error object is used; for testing only

Enums/UserType.html#/s:5TDLib8UserTypeO7.name: deleted
